2 Biodiversity

2.1 Generate community data

# Prepare each species abundance
rabit <- c(7, 10, 5, 8)
horse <- c(3, 0, 3, 1)
wolf <- c(0, 0, 2, 1)

# Generate data frame
df <- data.frame(sp1 = rabit, sp2 = horse, sp3 = wolf)

2.2 Species richness

richness <- rowSums(df > 0)

2.3 Shannon index

\[ H'=-\sum_{i=1}^{R}{p_i \ln{p_i}} \] , where \(p_i\) and \(R\) indicate the relative abundance of species \(i\) and species richness, respectively.

# Calculate relative abundance
rel_df <- df/rowSums(df)

# Calculate Shannon index Community 1 Simple summation
Sha_com1 <- -((rel_df[1, 1] * log(rel_df[1, 1])) + (rel_df[1, 2] * log(rel_df[1,
    2])))

### For loop
Sha_com1 <- 0
for (i in 1:2) {
    Sha_com1 <- Sha_com1 - (rel_df[1, i] * log(rel_df[1, i]))
}

## Community 2
Sha_com2 <- -(rel_df[2, 1] * log(rel_df[2, 1]))

## Community 3
Sha_com3 <- 0
for (i in 1:3) {
    Sha_com3 <- Sha_com3 - (rel_df[3, i] * log(rel_df[3, i]))
}

## Community 4
Sha_com4 <- 0
for (i in 1:3) {
    Sha_com4 <- Sha_com4 - (rel_df[4, i] * log(rel_df[4, i]))
}

# Show all
Sha_com1
[1] 0.6108643
Sha_com2
[1] 0
Sha_com3
[1] 1.029653
Sha_com4
[1] 0.6390319

2.4 (Gini) Simpson index

\[ 1-\lambda = 1-\sum_{i=1}^{R}{p_i^2} \]

## Community 1
simp_com1 <- 1 - sum(rel_df[1, ]^2)
## Community 2
simp_com2 <- 1 - sum(rel_df[2, ]^2)
## Community 3
simp_com3 <- 1 - sum(rel_df[3, ]^2)
## Community 4
simp_com4 <- 1 - sum(rel_df[4, ]^2)

# Show all
simp_com1
[1] 0.42
simp_com2
[1] 0
simp_com3
[1] 0.62
simp_com4
[1] 0.34

3 Population dynamics

3.1 Exponential Growth Model

\[ N_{t=0} = N_0　\\ N_{t+1} - N_t = rN_t \]

# Initial abundance
N0 <- 10

# Growth rate
r <- 0.5

# Set time limit
t_max <- 20

# Prepare an object that stores results
Nt <- rep(0, t_max)

# Growth model
Nt[1] <- N0
for (t in 1:t_max) {
    Nt[t + 1] <- Nt[t] + r * Nt[t]
}

# Visualize the result
plot(Nt, type = "b")

3.2 Discrete Logistic Model

\[ N_{t=0} = N_0　\\ N_{t+1} - N_t = rN_t(1-\frac{N_t}{K}) \]

# Initial abundance
N0 <- 10

# Growth rate
r <- 0.5

# Carrying Capacity
K <- 100

# Set time limit
t_max <- 20

# Prepare an object that stores results
Nt <- rep(0, t_max)

# Growth model
Nt[1] <- N0
for (t in 1:t_max) {
    Nt[t + 1] <- Nt[t] + r * Nt[t] * (1 - Nt[t]/K)
}

# Visualize the result
plot(Nt, type = "b")
